@user1:
Aaaah I figured it out! 

The reason test worked and hub build broke was because in tests `args.path` is specified with an absolute path - for example `hub_build_test` uses `os.path.join(cur_dir, 'hub-mwu')`, where `cur_dir` is an absolute path, while building in Jina Hub is done using relative paths, e.g. `encoders/audio/MFCCTimbreEncoder/`. 

Tests worked absolutely fine, but they were only done for the absolute path - where both `path` and `dockerfile` are absolute paths. If both are relative, then docker SDK tries to join them together, which doesn't work unless `dockerfile` is really just the name of the file inside `args.path`.

So yes, extracting the path using `os.path.basename` as you are doing now is the right way (btw you have to do it in another location in the file, that's why the CI is failing). All that should be added is a test where `args.path` is passed as a relative path, and we are good to go :D

